= 2 RESEARCH PROBLEM

#v(12pt)

The Robot Sumo community lacks any automated tools for match analysis. All assessment is manual, subjective, non-scalable, and leaves no permanent record. Historical knowledge from competitions is lost with each generation of competitors, and teams design new robots based on intuition without access to real combat data.

#v(1pt)

From a computer vision perspective, the domain of scenarios with extreme speed, ultra-short duration, and small visually similar objects remains underexplored in the literature. No prior work proposes an end-to-end pipeline for detection, tracking, and performance metric extraction in Robot Sumo.

#v(1pt)

No annotated datasets exist for this domain, preventing both systematic research and reproducible benchmarks.
